attributes.background:
1.Afghan farmers grow poppies as opposed to any other crop as it yields the highest profits 
2.The Taliban buy the crops and convert to heroin to fund ongoing conflicts 
3.The current approach of destroying crops is forcing farmers into joining the Taliban 
4.The UK has a diamorphine shortage 
5.Buying the poppies would: 
a.keep the farmers in farming rather than fighting;
b.end the diamorphine shortage in the UK;
c.reduce the income of the Taliban;
d.reduce the amount of street heroin; 
(This idea was originally proposed by the BMA in Jan 2007)
